 should give the process a bit of time','line_number':89,'multiline':False]['text':' to die gracefully if it needs it.','line_number':90,'multiline':False]['text':' Termination signals should kill the process quickly, as it's typically','line_number':93,'multiline':False]['text':' blocking the return of the prompt after a user hits "Ctrl-C". But we allow','line_number':94,'multiline':False]['text':' customizing the behavior of SIGTERM because it's used by the dynamic','line_number':95,'multiline':False]['text':' scheduler to terminate process trees in a controlled manner.','line_number':96,'multiline':False]['text':' On macOS, we have to ensure the whole process group is terminated before','line_number':111,'multiline':False]['text':' collecting the status of the PID we are interested in. (Otherwise other','line_number':112,'multiline':False]['text':' processes could race us and grab the PGID.)','line_number':113,'multiline':False]['text':' The child is done for, but may have grandchildren that we still have to','line_number':119,'multiline':False]['text':' kill.','line_number':120,'multiline':False]['text':' If we enabled the child subreaper feature (on Linux), now that we have','line_number':140,'multiline':False]['text':' collected the status of the PID we were interested in, terminate the','line_number':141,'multiline':False]['text':' rest of the process group and wait until all the children are gone.','line_number':142,'multiline':False]['text':'','line_number':143,'multiline':False]['text':' If you are wondering why we don't use a PID namespace instead, it's','line_number':144,'multiline':False]['text':' because those can have subtle effects on the processes we spawn (like','line_number':145,'multiline':False]['text':' them assuming that the PIDs that they get are unique). The linux-sandbox','line_number':146,'multiline':False]['text':' offers this functionality.','line_number':147,'multiline':False]['text':' The child is done for, but may have grandchildren that we still have to','line_number':152,'multiline':False]['text':' kill.','line_number':153,'multiline':False]['text':' Don't trust the exit code if we got a timeout or signal.','line_number':159,'multiline':False]['text':' Called when timeout or signal occurs.','line_number':171,'multiline':False]['text':' Called when timeout or signal occurs.','line_number':177,'multiline':False]